definitions.definition: To move out of a dwelling or other property , either by choice or by eviction .
examples: I have to vacate my house by midday, as the new owner is moving in.
You are hereby ordered to vacate the premises within 14 days.

definitions.definition: To leave an office or position .
examples: He vacated his coaching position because of the corruption scandal.

definitions.definition: To have a court judgement set aside ; to annul .
examples: The judge vacated the earlier decision when new evidence was presented.

definitions.definition: To leave an area , usually as a result of orders from public authorities in the event of a riot or natural disaster .
examples: If you do not immediately vacate the area, we will make you leave with tear gas!

main_definition: To move out of a dwelling or other property , either by choice or by eviction .
secondary_definitions: To leave an office or position .
